<item>
            <title>[JCR-727] NamespaceRegistryTest uses an invalid URI as namespace URI</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-727</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The test cases use &amp;quot;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.apache.org/&quot;&gt;www.apache.org/&lt;/a&gt;...&amp;quot; as a namespace URI, but this is not a URI.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Suggest to fix by using a proper URI, such as by prefixing with &amp;quot;http://&amp;quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
A related question is what our expectation is for JCR implementations. Are they allowed to reject something that doesn&amp;#39;t parse as a URI according to RFC3986?&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
